51.9	Democratic_peace_theory	Democratic peace theory	Democratic peace theory (or simply the "democratic peace") is the theory that democracies don't go to war with each other. How well the theory matches reality depends a great deal on one's definition of "democracy" and "war". For example,	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/43/Immanuel_Kant_%28painted_portrait%29.jpg/125px-Immanuel_Kant_%28painted_portrait%29.jpg
